Professional services rendered as follows :
1. D.P Remark
2. P.R Card
3. Preparation and drafting of legal documents such as 
    Common Consent, Individual Consent, Power of Attorney, 
    Individual Agreement, Development Agreements & Affidavit 
    for Annexure II. 
5. Hindi translation of Common Consent, Individual Consent, 
    Power of Attorney, Development Agreement ,Individual 
    Agreement & Affidavit.
6. Initial meeting with Nitesh and Others, discussing project 
    requirements.
7. Preparation of documents for Annexure I,II,III,IV,V,VI  for file 
    submission in SRA.
7. Assisting¬†in¬†Survey.

Scope Of Work 
1. AGM - Meeting held to pass key redevelopment resolutions 
    and appoint developer.
2. Development agreement - Legal agreement between society 
    and developer for the redevelopment project.
3. Individual consent - Given by each member for 
    redevelopment.
4. Power of Attorney - Allowing society/developer to act on 
     members‚Äô behalf.
5. Minute Book - Official record of all society meetings and 
    passed resolutions.
6. Individual Concept - Proposed flat plan and area shown to 
    each member.
7. Common Concept - Overall building layout including 
    amenities and common areas.
8. Survey - Site-wise measurement and documentation of all 
    tenements.
9. Submission - On Progress Step-wise submission of 
    documents and plans to SRA for approval.
10. SRA Portal Registration - Online registration of the project 
      and uploading of required documents.

Description of Services Rendered:
1.	Preparation of Architectural Plans for Rehab Building:
    Design and development of detailed architectural plans for     
    the rehabilitation building in accordance with SRA norms, 
    area statements, and other technical documentation as 
    required.
2.	Preparation of Municipal Drawings:
    Preparation and submission of required municipal drawings 
    for approvals from relevant authorities (including SRA, 
    MCGM, MHADA if applicable).
3.	Feasibility Report Preparation:
    Preparation of feasibility report based on site conditions, 
    existing structures, and DCR norms to determine project 
    viability.
4.	Preparation of Superimposed Plans:
    Preparation of existing vs proposed superimposed layout 
    plans for submission.
